1. Download all of your lecture slides
 
2. Go to Quizlet.com, sign-up for an account
 
3. Go to quizlet.com/notes/upload, click "File from computer" and upload one lecture slide
 
4. Read the overview, do the flashcards, and then do the test. Do not move onto the next lecture slides until you get 100% on the practice test
 
5. Go back to quizlet.com/notes/upload, "File from computer" and upload another lecture slide
 
6. Read the overview, do the flashcards, and then do the test. After successfully getting 100% on this lecture slide, go back to the PREVIOUS lecture slide and do the flashcards and test.
 
Example:
 
Slide 1: 100%, move onto slide 2.
Slide 2: 100%, go back to slide 1.
Slide 1: 100%, move onto slide 3.
Slide 3: 100%, go back to slide 2.
Slide 2: 100%, go back to slide 1.
Slide 1: 100%, move onto slide 4.
Slide 4: 100%, go back to slide 3.
Slide 3: 100%, go back to slide 2.
Slide 2: 100%, go back to slide 1.
Slide 1: 100%, move onto slide 5.
Slide 5: 100%, go back to slide 4.
Slide 4: 100%, go back to slide 3.
Slide 3: 100%, go back to slide 2.
Slide 2: 100%, go back to slide 1.
Slide 1: 100%, move onto slide 6. 
 
Repeat until you have done all slides.

